Insert a character 'ch' at position 'i' (Zero Based indexing) .

Method 1: Using Iterators
          Syntax - stringname.insert(iterator,character);
          Example - string str = "abcd";
                    str.insert(str.begin()+2,'e');
                    //str = abecd;
          Exceptions - Undefined behaviour if iterator points after/before string .
        
Method 2: Using index
          Syntax - stringname.insert(position,number_of_times_to_be_inserted,character);
          Example - string str = "abcd";
                    str.insert(1,4,'y');
                    //str = ayyyybcd;
          Exceptions - Undefined behaviour if index is greater than string length.
